            <thetext>There&apos;s a request in the FastMail bug tracker for support for sieve variables.  It would be a great thing to have in upstream Cyrus, so I&apos;m moving the request out here.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <who name="Kevin Ballard">kevin@sb.org</who>
            <bug_when>2014-09-22 19:34:42 EDT</bug_when>
            <thetext>I made the request :) The sieve variables extension would be extremely helpful to me. I get a *lot* of email from GitHub due to watching multiple repositories (one of them being especially high-traffic). Without sieve variables, I have to hard-code the list of repositories I can filter on into my Sieve file, which is fragile and also duplicates a lot of code. Sieve variables would let me calculate the appropriate mailbox name instead, which would save a lot of code and transparently support new repositories.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
